## 🛠️ DFIR Tools You Must Know

### Essential Tools by Category

**DISK IMAGING & HASHING:**
```
FTK Imager
├─ Windows, Mac, Linux
├─ Create forensic images (E01, dd, AFF formats)
├─ Hash verification (MD5, SHA1, SHA256)
├─ File recovery from unallocated space
└─ FREE

Guymager
├─ Linux-based
├─ Faster imaging than FTK on Linux
├─ AES encryption support
└─ FREE

dd (command-line)
├─ Linux/Mac
├─ if=/dev/sda of=/media/usb/disk.img (full disk image)
├─ if=/dev/sda1 of=/media/usb/partition.img (single partition)
└─ FREE
```

**MEMORY ANALYSIS:**
```
Volatility 3
├─ Windows, Mac, Linux memory analysis
├─ Find running processes, injected code, network connections
├─ Extract malware from RAM
├─ pslist, pstree, netscan, yarascan (key commands)
└─ FREE

DumpIt / Belkasoft RAM Capturer
├─ Quick memory dumps from running systems
├─ Before shutting down (preserve volatile evidence!)
└─ FREE/Commercial
```

**TIMELINE CONSTRUCTION:**
```
Plaso (log2timeline)
├─ Linux-based
├─ Parses events from disk image + logs
├─ Outputs to CSV/timeline
└─ FREE

Timeline Explorer (SANS)
├─ Windows GUI
├─ Import/filter/search timelines
├─ Color-code events
└─ FREE

Autopsy
├─ Visual forensic platform
├─ Disk image analysis
├─ Timeline generation
├─ Keyword search
└─ FREE
```

**REGISTRY ANALYSIS:**
```
RegRipper
├─ Windows registry analysis
├─ Extract Run keys, MRU lists, USB history
├─ Plugins for each analysis type
└─ FREE

Registry Explorer (Eric Zimmerman)
├─ Modern registry viewer
├─ Timeline from registry LastWrite times
├─ Search across all hives
└─ FREE
```

**LOG ANALYSIS:**
```
Windows Event Log Parser
├─ Parse .evtx files offline
├─ Filter by EventID, timestamp, user
├─ Export to CSV
└─ FREE (built-in or powershell)

Splunk / ELK / GreyLog
├─ Aggregate logs from multiple sources
├─ Search + pivot
├─ Create timelines from log timestamps
└─ Commercial/FREE (ELK)
```

**PRACTICAL EXAMPLE:**

```
Investigation workflow using tools:

1. Image compromised disk
   └─ FTK Imager: Create E01 image, verify hash

2. Extract memory dump (if still running)
   └─ DumpIt: Capture RAM before shutdown

3. Mount forensic image (read-only)
   └─ FTK Imager or loopback mount

4. Parse events from image
   └─ Plaso: Extract all timestamps into CSV

5. Analyze memory dump
   └─ Volatility: volatility3 -f memory.dump windows.pslist
      (find suspicious processes, injected code)

6. Extract registry hives
   └─ RegRipper: rip.pl -r C:\Windows\System32\config\SYSTEM
      (extract Run keys, last login time, etc)

7. Build master timeline
   └─ Timeline Explorer: Import CSV from Plaso, add manual entries from Volatility/RegRipper

8. Analyze timeline
   ├─ Look for sequences (login → payload → execution → persistence)
   ├─ Cross-reference with network logs (did attacker C2?)
   └─ Identify root cause

9. Generate report
   └─ Document findings with evidence + hashes + screenshots
```

