## 🔗 How DFIR Connects to Everything

```
Detection Engineering
├─ Finds the attack (SIEM alert)
└─ DFIR analyzes it, finds root cause
   └─ Detection Engineer writes rule to catch similar attacks in future

Incident Response
├─ Decides in real-time (isolate? not yet?)
└─ DFIR does detailed investigation
   └─ IR uses DFIR findings for containment decisions

Threat Hunting
├─ Hunts for suspicious patterns
└─ If finds something, escalates to DFIR
   └─ DFIR confirms it's real attack or false positive

Network Security
├─ Logs all traffic
└─ DFIR analyzes firewall/IDS logs for C2 connections
   └─ Used to trace attacker's exfiltration path

Endpoint Security (EDR/AV)
├─ Blocks malware, records behavior
└─ DFIR analyzes EDR logs for attack timeline
   └─ Combined with disk/memory forensics = complete picture

Compliance (SOC 2, HIPAA, PCI-DSS)
├─ Requires incident investigation
└─ DFIR provides documented proof
   └─ "Here's the timeline, chain of custody, evidence"
```

